article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- — Ebby Asamoah had 24 points in East Tennessee State's 70-57 victory against Kansas City on Wednesday night. Asamoah also had six rebounds and three blocks for the Buccaneers (7-4). Jaden Seymour scored 12 points and added seven rebounds. Jadyn Parker had 11 points and was 3 of 9 shooting and 5 of 7 from the free throw line. Cameron Faas led the way for the Roos (5-8) with 12 points and eight rebounds. Jamar Brown added 12 points and seven rebounds for Kansas City. In addition, Khristion Courseault had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
